{
    "id": "astronomy/basic-telescope",
    "title": "Assemble a Simple Telescope",
    "description": "Use 50 mm and 20 mm magnifying lenses, masking tape, a cardboard mailing tube and a camera tripod to build a simple refractor for viewing Jupiter's moons. Work in the shade and never aim at the Sun.",
    "image": "/assets/quests/simple_cardboard_telescope_assembly.jpg",
    "npc": "/assets/npc/nova.jpg",
    "start": "start",
    "dialogue": [
        {
            "id": "start",
            "text": "Nova here. Gather a 50 mm lens, 20 mm lens, mailing tube, masking tape, and a camera tripod. Inspect for chips, work in shade, wear eye protection, and keep the tube away from the Sun. Ready?",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "build",
                    "text": "I'm ready.",
                    "requiresItems": [
                        {
                            "id": "0254a829-9002-4a75-8af2-03cd961601da",
                            "count": 1
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "7aafe032-86e2-449e-8e25-8148f8c58c17",
                            "count": 1
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "2794503d-fbe7-4031-a63e-deac531f9784",
                            "count": 1
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "49fb255e-a4c3-48e4-bca7-4c3781fdb98b",
                            "count": 1
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "13aaff4f-e4ba-4e4a-b21b-5852b118a0ed",
                            "count": 1
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "build",
            "text": "Choose your assembly path: direct tube build or pre-mount both lenses before seating the tube. Keep fingers clear of glass edges and keep the scope capped until night use.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "process",
                    "process": "assemble-basic-telescope",
                    "text": "Build the direct tube assembly."
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "alternate-build",
                    "text": "Use the staged pre-mount method first."
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "verify",
                    "text": "Assembly complete; verify image quality.",
                    "requiresItems": [
                        {
                            "id": "f439b57a-9df3-4bd9-9b6e-042476ceecf5",
                            "count": 1
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "alternate-build",
            "text": "Pre-seat each lens with light tape, then secure both ends after checking the optical axis. If wobble appears, return to direct build and retighten before field use.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "process",
                    "process": "assemble-basic-telescope",
                    "text": "Run staged pre-mount assembly now."
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "verify",
                    "text": "Staged build done; start verification.",
                    "requiresItems": [
                        {
                            "id": "f439b57a-9df3-4bd9-9b6e-042476ceecf5",
                            "count": 1
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "build",
                    "text": "The mount still shifts - back to direct build checks."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "verify",
            "text": "Point at Jupiter only after sunset. Confirm moons are distinct points and the tripod stays stable for a full minute.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "finish",
                    "text": "Verified: stable tripod and clear moon points.",
                    "requiresItems": [
                        {
                            "id": "f439b57a-9df3-4bd9-9b6e-042476ceecf5",
                            "count": 1
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "troubleshoot",
                    "text": "Image is blurry or the mount drifts."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "troubleshoot",
            "text": "Pause observing. Re-cap the objective, retension tripod joints, and re-seat the eyepiece. If glass is chipped or loose, stop and rebuild before any further viewing.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "build",
                    "text": "Rebuild safely from the assembly step."
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "verify",
                    "text": "Hardware corrected - re-run verification."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "finish",
            "text": "Excellent craftsmanship. Regular stargazing sharpens navigation. Cap both lenses before storing and keep the telescope away from heat and direct sunlight.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "finish",
                    "text": "Thanks, Nova."
                }
            ]
        }
    ],
